 $\\theta = [\\pi/6]$ case\nproduce a discrete shedding frequency instead of a broadened one, as told\nbefore. The shedding frequency increases to a maximum of $[fL/u_\\infty] \\sim\n0.26$ for the maximum slit size of $\\xi = 0.5$. More insights on the shedding\nvortices, momentum deficit in the wake, varying energy contents in the flow\nfield, and the dominant spatiotemporal structures are also provided.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 25 Apr 2022 19:37:00 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-06-29"}
