y alone that align\nfunctionally similar proteins with p-values in some cases below 1e-300. We\npredict that topological network alignment has a bright future as edge\ndensities increase towards the value where good alignments become possible. We\ndemonstrate that when enough common topology is present at high enough edge\ndensities-for example in the recent, partly synthetic networks of the\nIntegrated Interaction Database-topological network alignment easily recovers\nmost orthologs, paving the way towards high-throughput functional prediction\nbased on topology-driven network alignment.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 25 Apr 2022 23:44:13 GMT"}],"update_date":"2022-08-29"}
