{"id":"2204.12098","submitter":"Jun Seok Oh","authors":"Gyu Whan Chang and Jun Seok Oh","title":"Prime Factorization of ideals in commutative rings, with a focus on\n  Krull rings","comments":"To appear in J. Korean Math. Soc","journal-ref":"J. Korean Math. Soc. 2023; 60(2): 407-464","doi":"10.4134/JKMS.j220271","report-no":null,"categories":"math.AC","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  Let $R$ be a commutative ring with identity. The structure theorem says that\n$R$ is a PIR (resp., UFR, general ZPI-ring, $\\pi$-ring) if and only if $R$ is a\nfinite direct product of PIDs (resp., UFDs, Dedekind domains, $\\pi$-domains)\nand special primary rings. All of these four types of integral domains are\nKrull domains, so motivated by the structure theorem, we study the prime\nfactorization of ideals in a ring that is a finite direct product of Krull\ndomains and special primary rings. Such a ring will be called a general Krull\nring. It is known that Krull domains can be characterized by the star\noperations $v$ or $t$ as follows: An integral domain $R$ is a Krull domain if\nand only if every nonzero proper principal ideal of $R$ can be written as a\nfinite $v$- or $t$-product of prime ideals. However, this is not true for\ngeneral Krull rings. In this paper, we introduce a new star operation $u$ on\n$R$, so that $R$ is a general Krull ring if and only if every proper principal\nideal of $R$ can be written as a finite $u$-product of prime ideals. We also\nstudy several ring-theoretic properties of general Krull rings including\nKaplansky-type theorem, Mori-Nagata theorem, Nagata rings, and Noetherian\nproperty.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 26 Apr 2022 06:26:27 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 5 Jan 2023 06:23:29 GMT"}],"update_date":"2023-03-13"}
